8 SECTION 3. NEW AND VACANT FTE POOL - BUDGET SECTION REPORT.
9 1. The legislative council may not spend funds from the new and vacant FTE pool line
10 item in subdivision 2 of section 1 of this Act, but may transfer funds from this line item
11 to the salaries and wages line item as necessary to provide funding for:
12 a. Filling a new FTE position from the date of hire through the end of the biennium;
13 or
14 b. Salaries and wages if actual salaries and wages savings from vacant positions
15 and employee turnover adjusted for other uses are less than the estimate used
16 by the sixty-ninth legislative assembly in the development of the appropriation.
17 2. The legislative council shall report to the budget section regarding the use of funding
18 in the pool including information on:
19 a. New FTE positions, including the date hired;
20 b. Vacant FTE positions, including information on positions that become vacant and
21 positions filled, salaries and wages savings resulting from vacant positions and
22 employee turnover, and the use of salaries and wages savings for other
23 purposes; and
24 c. Additional salaries and wages funding needed due to savings from vacant
25 positions being less than anticipated.
26 3. If funding in the new and vacant FTE pool line item is insufficient to provide the
27 necessary salaries and wages funding for the biennium, the legislative council may
28 request a deficiency appropriation from the seventieth legislative assembly.
