19 SECTION 6. AMENDMENT. Section 48-08-04 of the North Dakota Century Code is
20 amended and reenacted as follows:
21 48-08-04. Use of legislative assembly rooms, and halls, and other space in the
22 capitol.
23 During the interim between legislative sessions, the committee rooms, halls, passageways,
24 and other space in the capitol used by the legislative assembly, including the pioneer room, the
25 coteau room, the Sheyenne River room, judicial wing room 216, and judicial wing rooms 327 B,
26 C, and E, may not be used without authorization of the legislative council. The fifteenth floor of
27 the capitol is reserved for the exclusive use of the legislative council.
